---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
	title="Privacy Policy | URLX"
	description="Privacy policy for URLX, a no-account URL shortener."
>
	<section class="bg-white">
		<div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-[800px] px-6 py-16">
			<p class="text-[14px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.06em] text-ink-2">
				Last updated June 14, 2026
			</p>
			<h1 class="mt-3 text-[40px] font-semibold leading-tight text-ink">
				Privacy Policy
			</h1>
			<div class="mt-8 space-y-8 text-[16px] leading-7 text-ink-2">
				<section>
					<h2 class="text-[22px] font-semibold text-ink">Overview</h2>
					<p class="mt-3">
						URLX is a no-account URL shortener. You do not need to create an
						account, provide an email address, or make a payment to create a
						short link.
					</p>
					<p class="mt-3">
						This policy describes the data URLX handles when you use the site
						and API. It is written for the current product behavior: no ads, no
						analytics SDK, and no cookies set by URLX.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2 class="text-[22px] font-semibold text-ink">Data We Handle</h2>
					<ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
						<li>
							Submitted URLs: when you shorten a link, URLX stores the original
							URL, a normalized version, a URL hash, the generated short code,
							and timestamps so the short link can work.
						</li>
						<li>
							Redirect data: when someone opens a short link, URLX looks up the
							short code and redirects the visitor to the stored destination.
						</li>
						<li>
							Optional browser history: if you choose "Remember recent URLs on
							this device", recent submitted URLs are stored in your browser's
							local storage. They are not sent to URLX as a separate history
							list.
						</li>
						<li>
							Operational logs: the server and hosting provider may process
							request metadata such as request path, response status, IP address,
							user agent, timing, and security-related metadata for operations,
							debugging, abuse prevention, and security.
						</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2 class="text-[22px] font-semibold text-ink">Cookies And Storage</h2>
					<p class="mt-3">
						URLX does not currently set cookies and does not currently use ad or
						analytics trackers.
					</p>
					<p class="mt-3">
						URLX can use browser local storage only if you opt in to remembering
						recent URLs on your device. You can turn this off or clear recent
						URLs from the homepage controls.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2 class="text-[22px] font-semibold text-ink">How We Use Data</h2>
					<ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
						<li>Create and serve short links.</li>
						<li>Return an existing short link for the same normalized URL.</li>
						<li>Prevent local, private-network, and unsupported URL schemes.</li>
						<li>Operate, secure, debug, and improve the service.</li>
						<li>Investigate abuse reports and disable harmful links.</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2 class="text-[22px] font-semibold text-ink">Third-Party Processing</h2>
					<p class="mt-3">
						URLX is built for Cloudflare infrastructure, including Cloudflare
						Workers and Cloudflare D1. Cloudflare may process hosting,
						security, database, and request metadata needed to provide the
						service.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2 class="text-[22px] font-semibold text-ink">Retention</h2>
					<p class="mt-3">
						Short-link records are kept while the short link remains active or
						as needed for operations, security, abuse handling, or legal
						requirements. Recent URLs saved in your browser remain on your
						device until you clear them, turn off the feature, clear site data,
						or use browser controls to remove local storage.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2 class="text-[22px] font-semibold text-ink">Your Choices</h2>
					<ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
						<li>You can use URLX without creating an account.</li>
						<li>You can leave recent URL history disabled.</li>
						<li>You can clear recent URLs from the homepage.</li>
						<li>You can avoid submitting URLs that contain sensitive personal data.</li>
						<li>
							You can report an abusive short link to the URLX maintainers using
							the maintainer links in the footer.
						</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2 class="text-[22px] font-semibold text-ink">Security</h2>
					<p class="mt-3">
						URLX validates submitted destination URLs, rejects unsupported
						schemes, rejects localhost and private-network addresses, and uses
						security headers on server responses. No internet service can be
						guaranteed to be perfectly secure.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2 class="text-[22px] font-semibold text-ink">Children</h2>
					<p class="mt-3">
						URLX is not directed to children and does not knowingly collect
						children's personal information.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2 class="text-[22px] font-semibold text-ink">Changes</h2>
					<p class="mt-3">
						If URLX changes how it collects, stores, or shares data, this policy
						should be updated before or when those changes go live.
					</p>
				</section>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
